    feat(ui): Redesign PrinterDetailView and standardize mod workflow

    This commit introduces a major redesign of the Printer Detail page to align its UI/UX with the rest of the application, creating a more consistent and modern user experience. The previous layout was a simple vertical stack, which resulted in wasted space on wider screens. The new design uses a responsive two-column grid with styled cards and headers.

    Additionally, the workflow for adding and editing printer mods has been refactored from modals into dedicated full-page views, standardizing the create/edit pattern across the entire application.

    Key changes include:

    -   **Redesigned PrinterDetailView Layout:**
        -   Replaced the single-column layout with a responsive two-column grid using styled cards.
        -   Consolidated "Printer Details" and "Notes" into a single card.
        -   Consolidated "Maintenance" and "Maintenance Notes" into another card.
        -   Standardized all button sizes on the page for visual consistency.

    -   **Standardized Mod Workflow:**
        -   Removed the "Add Mod" and "Edit Mod" modals.
        -   Created new dedicated views (`ModCreateView.vue`, `ModEditView.vue`) for a consistent full-page form experience.
        -   Created a reusable `ModForm.vue` component and standardized its styling to match other forms.

    -   **New "Download All" Feature for Mods:**
        -   Added a "Download All" button to each mod with files.
        -   Implemented a backend endpoint to zip and serve the files.
        -   Added a loading spinner to the button to provide user feedback during the download.

    -   **Code Hygiene & Bug Fixes:**
        -   Centralized common styles (`.form-control`, `.btn-delete-file`) into `main.css`.
        -   Added functionality to remove files from the upload queue in the mod form.
        -   Fixed various UI bugs, including input field autofill colors, file upload behavior, and text spacing.
