[33mcommit ca9b11a15e3ec35f6e687b97218e0778a3c60c41[m
Author: Jason Jennings <jdjennings@gmail.com>
Date: Sat Aug 16 15:10:34 2025 -0700

    Increases the maximum file upload size to 250MB to support the restoration of large backup archives via the UI.

    The default Nginx limit of 1MB was causing "413 Request Entity Too Large" errors when uploading larger backup files. This commit raises the limit in both the Nginx proxy and the Django backend to ensure large files can be processed successfully.

    - `frontend/nginx.conf`: Sets `client_max_body_size` to 250m.
    - `backend/settings.py`: Sets `DATA_UPLOAD_MAX_MEMORY_SIZE` to the equivalent value in bytes.

